&quot;Doc Miller&quot;<br><br>
I find it difficult to pay enough proper respect to Medics/Corpsmen.  You're idea of saving a young American's life was to run or crawl to them and administer life saving assistance.  Many of these combat casualties lived to suffer little or no physical hindrance in the remainder of their lives.<br>
&quot;Dock&quot; (Dock... as in wharf rat) Spatz's idea of saving young American males was to sacrifice their dignity and honor. Something that he does with great fecundity, because he never had any dignity or honor to forfiet, therefore he sees no reason for others to have any.  As a matter of fact, your honor and dignity is a threat to him.<br>
Spatz is not a &quot;has been&quot;...he is more of a &quot;never was&quot; and a &quot;never will be!&quot;<br>
I am, at once, angered, amused and depressed by Dock Spatz.  His continious filthy language and unwarranted attacks on combat veterans assails my senses.  The ridiculous justifications for his postulations make me laugh.  He is anti-God, anti-war, anti-everything... which leads me to believe that he is anti-self.  However, he is all for taking advantage of the priviledges guaranteed by our sacred institutions.  He simply does not want to pay his share... now or then.  He is pro-filthy language and pro-criticism.<br>
&quot;Welcome Home, Doc Tex Miller!&quot;<br><br>
